Male genitalia (
Fig. 22
): Moderately sclerotized. Median lobe slender, moderately arcuate, not twisted, apex stick-like. Endophallus without visible teeth. Parameres of about same length, both slender, each distorted anterior apex, with minute seta preapically.

Female genitalia. (
Fig. 34
): Coxostylus slender, nearly straight in basal part, gently curved to apex, with short obtuse knob-like tooth dorsally at base, with one seta preapically, with one blunt and one acute short ensiform seta, with five nematiform setae. Ramus of moderate size.

Distribution: Known from the Luzon Island (
Philippines
).
